        <div class="equation-hero">
            <h1>The Pneuma Lagrangian</h1>
            <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.1rem; max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;">
                The fundamental fermionic field term that sources all of physics - from spacetime geometry to matter content.
            </p>
            <div class="main-equation">
                S = &int; d<sup>26</sup>X &radic;(-G) [R + <span style="text-decoration: overline;">&Psi;</span><sub>P</sub> (i&Gamma;<sup>M</sup>D<sub>M</sub> - m)&Psi;<sub>P</sub>]
            </div>
            <p style="color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.9rem; margin-top: 1rem;">
                <strong>Full 26D:</strong> 8192-component spinor, Cl(24,2) Clifford algebra, Sp(2,R) gauge<br>
                <strong>Effective 13D:</strong> 64-component spinor via gauge fixing, Cl(12,1)<br>
                <strong>Fermionic primacy</strong> - Pneuma spinor sources all physics
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Expandable Formula with Derivation Chain -->
        <div class="expandable-formula">
            <div class="formula-header">
