                <div class="term-card">
                    <div class="term-symbol">&beta;<sub>F</sub> = 0.15</div>
                    <h4>Matter Coupling</h4>
                    <p>
                        Coupling to stress-energy trace T. Dimensionless parameter affecting matter-geometry interaction.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="term-card">
                    <div class="term-symbol">&gamma;<sub>F</sub> = 0.0001 M<sub>Pl</sub><sup>-2</sup></div>
                    <h4>Two-Time Invariant</h4>
                    <p>
                        Coupling to orthogonal time invariant &tau;. Small value consistent with thermal time hypothesis.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="term-card">
                    <div class="term-symbol">&delta;<sub>F</sub> = 10<sup>-19</sup> s</div>
                    <h4>Dynamical Evolution</h4>
                    <p>
                        Time-varying coupling (&part;<sub>t</sub>&tau;)R. Extremely small - near Planck timescale effects.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3>4. Mashiach Attractor Lagrangian</h3>
            <p>
                The dark energy sector is described by the Mashiach scalar field with late-time attractor dynamics
                ensuring w &rarr; -1.0:
            </p>

            <div class="interactive-formula" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(255, 126, 182, 0.12), rgba(139, 127, 255, 0.08)); border: 2px solid rgba(255, 126, 182, 0.4); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0;">
                <span class="formula-hint">Hover for details</span>
                <div class="formula-display" style="display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; gap: 0.4rem; font-size: 1.25rem; flex-wrap: wrap;">
                    <span class="formula-var" style="background: rgba(255, 126, 182, 0.2); padding: 0.3rem 0.6rem; border-radius: 6px;">&Lscr;<sub>&phi;</sub>
                        <div class="var-tooltip">
                            <div class="var-name">&Lscr;<sub>&phi;</sub> - Scalar Field Lagrangian</div>
                            <div class="var-desc">Mashiach quintessence-like dark energy field</div>
                        </div>
                    </span>
                    <span class="formula-op">=</span>
                    <span class="formula-op">-</span>
                    <span class="formula-var" style="background: rgba(139, 127, 255, 0.2); padding: 0.3rem 0.5rem; border-radius: 6px;">&frac12;(&part;&phi;)<sup>2</sup>
                        <div class="var-tooltip">
                            <div class="var-name">Kinetic Term</div>
                            <div class="var-desc">Standard canonical kinetic energy for scalar field</div>
                        </div>
                    </span>
                    <span class="formula-op">-</span>
                    <span class="formula-var" style="background: rgba(81, 207, 102, 0.2); padding: 0.3rem 0.5rem; border-radius: 6px;">V(&phi;)
                        <div class="var-tooltip">
                            <div class="var-name">V(&phi;) - Potential</div>
                            <div class="var-desc">Attractor potential with late-time minimum</div>
                        </div>
                    </span>
                </div>
                <div class="formula-label" style="text-align: center; margin-top: 1rem; color: var(--text-muted);">
                    Mashiach Attractor Lagrangian
                </div>
            </div>

            <p>
                The potential V(&phi;) is constructed to have a stable late-time attractor:
            </p>

            <div class="interactive-formula" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(81, 207, 102, 0.12), rgba(139, 127, 255, 0.08)); border: 2px solid rgba(81, 207, 102, 0.4); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0;">
                <span class="formula-hint">Hover for details</span>
                <div class="formula-display" style="display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; gap: 0.4rem; font-size: 1.2rem; flex-wrap: wrap;">
                    <span class="formula-var" style="background: rgba(81, 207, 102, 0.2); padding: 0.3rem 0.6rem; border-radius: 6px;">V(&phi;<sub>M</sub>)
                        <div class="var-tooltip">
                            <div class="var-name">V(&phi;<sub>M</sub>) - Mashiach Potential</div>
                            <div class="var-desc">Potential evaluated at Mashiach field &phi;<sub>M</sub></div>
                        </div>
                    </span>
                    <span class="formula-op">=</span>
                    <span class="formula-var" style="background: rgba(255, 126, 182, 0.2); padding: 0.3rem 0.6rem; border-radius: 6px;">V<sub>0</sub>
                        <div class="var-tooltip">
                            <div class="var-name">V<sub>0</sub> - Vacuum Energy Scale</div>
                            <div class="var-desc">Sets the cosmological constant scale &Lambda;</div>
                        </div>
                    </span>
                    <span class="formula-op">[</span>
                    <span class="formula-var" style="padding: 0.2rem 0.4rem;">1
                        <div class="var-tooltip">
                            <div class="var-name">Constant Term</div>
                            <div class="var-desc">Baseline vacuum energy</div>
                        </div>
                    </span>
                    <span class="formula-op">+</span>
                    <span class="formula-var" style="background: rgba(139, 127, 255, 0.2); padding: 0.3rem 0.5rem; border-radius: 6px;">A cos(&omega;&phi;<sub>M</sub>/f)
                        <div class="var-tooltip">
                            <div class="var-name">Modulation Term</div>
                            <div class="var-desc">Oscillatory component from axion-like structure</div>
                        </div>
                    </span>
                    <span class="formula-op">]</span>
                </div>
                <div class="formula-label" style="text-align: center; margin-top: 1rem; color: var(--text-muted);">
                    Mashiach Potential with Attractor Structure
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="term-breakdown" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));">
                <div class="term-card">
                    <div class="term-symbol">&phi;<sub>M</sub> = 2.493 M<sub>Pl</sub></div>
                    <h4>Mashiach VEV</h4>
                    <p>
                        Derived value from weighted KKLT/LVS/topology methods. Central value with error ~5.0.
                        Physical range: 0.5 - 5.0 M<sub>Pl</sub>.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="term-card">
                    <div class="term-symbol">w &rarr; -1.0</div>
                    <h4>Late-Time Attractor</h4>
                    <p>
                        Equation of state approaches &Lambda;CDM limit: w = -1.0 exactly at the potential minimum.
                        Resolves DE fine-tuning problem.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="term-card">
                    <div class="term-symbol">V<sub>0</sub></div>
                    <h4>Vacuum Energy Scale</h4>
                    <p>
                        Sets &Lambda; ~ (2.4 meV)<sup>4</sup> to match observed dark energy density &rho;<sub>&Lambda;</sub> ~ 10<sup>-47</sup> GeV<sup>4</sup>.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="term-card">
                    <div class="term-symbol">A, &omega;, f</div>
                    <h4>Potential Parameters</h4>
                    <p>
                        A: amplitude of modulation; &omega;: frequency; f: decay constant.
                        Tuned for slow-roll and attractor dynamics.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="physics-note">
                <h4>Attractor Dynamics</h4>
                <p>
                    The Mashiach field &phi; evolves according to the Klein-Gordon equation in an FRW background:
                    <br><br>
                    <span style="font-family: 'Crimson Text', serif; font-size: 1.1rem;">
                        &ddot;&phi; + 3H&dot;&phi; + V'(&phi;) = 0
                    </span>
                    <br><br>
                    At late times, the field rolls to the minimum of V(&phi;), where &dot;&phi; &rarr; 0, yielding
                    w = -1.0 without fine-tuning. This is the <strong>attractor solution</strong> - independent of
                    initial conditions.
                </p>
            </div>

            <h3>Summary: The Lagrangian Cascade</h3>
            <p>
                The complete descent from fundamental 26D physics to 4D observables:
            </p>

            <div class="equation-box" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(255, 126, 182, 0.08), rgba(139, 127, 255, 0.08)); border: 2px solid rgba(255, 126, 182, 0.3);">
                <strong style="color: var(--accent-secondary);">Level 1 (26D):</strong>
                S = &int; d<sup>26</sup>X &radic;(-G) [R + <span style="text-decoration: overline;">&Psi;</span><sub>P</sub> (i&Gamma;<sup>M</sup>D<sub>M</sub> - m)&Psi;<sub>P</sub>]
                <br><br>
                <span style="font-size: 1.5rem; color: var(--text-muted);">&darr;</span> Sp(2,R) gauge fixing
                <br><br>
                <strong style="color: var(--accent-primary);">Level 2 (13D):</strong>
                &Lscr;<sub>13D</sub> = M<sub>*</sub><sup>11</sup> R<sub>13D</sub> + <span style="text-decoration: overline;">&Psi;</span><sub>64</sub> (i&gamma;<sup>&mu;</sup>&nabla;<sub>&mu;</sub> - m<sub>eff</sub>)&Psi;<sub>64</sub> + &Lscr;<sub>flux</sub>
                <br><br>
                <span style="font-size: 1.5rem; color: var(--text-muted);">&darr;</span> KK reduction (13D &rarr; 4D)
                <br><br>
                <strong style="color: #51cf66;">Level 3 (4D):</strong>
                f(R,T,&tau;) = R + &alpha;<sub>F</sub>R<sup>2</sup> + &beta;<sub>F</sub>T + &gamma;<sub>F</sub>R&tau; + &delta;<sub>F</sub>(&part;<sub>t</sub>&tau;)R
                <br><br>
                <strong style="color: #ff7eb6;">Level 4 (DE):</strong>
                &Lscr;<sub>&phi;</sub> = -&frac12;(&part;&phi;)<sup>2</sup> - V(&phi;<sub>M</sub>), &nbsp; V = V<sub>0</sub>[1 + A cos(&omega;&phi;<sub>M</sub>/f)]
                <span class="equation-label">Complete Lagrangian Hierarchy</span>
            </div>
        </section>

